summaries.short: Ray and Tanya reach a professional crossroads after Lenore's 'test drive.'
summaries.full: Ray's fortunes sink further when his nosy neighbor, Howard Koontz, accuses him of public indecency. Fed up with Jessica's maternal meddling, Damon and Darby yearn to go back to their dad's. Meanwhile, Ray and Tanya's frayed partnership seems to be dead in the water--until a last-minute proposal resurrects their dreams.

summaries.short: Ray debates whether to follow through on Tanya's leads; Damon overreacts while defending Darby's honor.
summaries.full: West Lakefield students choose 'Coach Ray' to be the recipient of their fall fundraising efforts.Tanya's got a couple of leads that could jump-start Ray's gigolo career. But is Ray ready, willing and able enough to follow through? Meanwhile, Damon is shattered when he rushes to his sister's defense, only to learn that Darby doesn't want his help.

summaries.short: Tanya maps out a strategy for Ray to attract a higher level of clientele.
summaries.full: In an effort to market Ray as a high-end 'happiness consultant,' Tanya tracks down a former law-firm colleague named Lenore, who agrees to take Ray for a test ride in exchange for the names and numbers of wealthy women. Meanwhile, Jessica's obsessive behavior grates on her kids, who push Ray to fix his fire-damaged house.

summaries.short: (Series Premiere) A divorced high-school basketball coach looks to change his fortunes by cashing in on his 'winning tool.'
summaries.full: (Series Premiere) Ray Drecker is a divorced high-school basketball coach whose fortunes have reached an all-time low. Lonely, run-down and at wit's end, Ray attends a self-help class whose mantra is to identify a personal winning tool to market for success. With the help of his ex-flame Tanya, Ray resolves to take advantage of his greatest asset: his 'winning tool.'
